text: Orland is an unincorporated community in Treutlen County, in the U.S. state of Georgia. ==History== A post office called Orland was established in 1902, and remained in operation until 1933. The Georgia General Assembly incorporated Orland as a town in 1908. The town's municipal charter was dissolved in 1915. ==References== Category:Former municipalities in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Unincorporated communities in Treutlen County, Georgia Category:Populated places disestablished in 1915
